Aqua America Inc. (WTR) , the second-biggest
U.S. water utility by market value, said units in Texas and
Illinois acquired three water companies and a wastewater system
to raise to 18 its purchases in 2012.  The acquisitions included Wingert Water Systems Inc. in
Comal County and Royal Oaks Water System Inc. in Kerr County,
Texas, and the Ilinois wastewater assets of Tri Star Estates in
Bourbonnais and water assets of the Moecherville Water District
in Kane County for about $3.8 million total, the  Bryn Mawr ,
Pennsylvania-based company said in a statement. American Water
